<li id="fn1"><p>In Prose, in non-articular phrases, when the genitive is
non-articular, the ratio is 55% preposed, 45% postposed; when it is
articular, the ratio changes to 29% preposed and 72% postposed. In
articular phrases the numbers for non-articular genitives are 18%
preposed, 46% internal, 36% postposed, and for articular genitives they
are 10% preposed, 38% internal, and 52% postposed.<a href="#fnref1" class="footnote-back" role="doc-backlink">↩︎</a></p></li>
<li id="fn2"><p>In non-articular phrases: 29% preposed and 71% postposed
non-articular genitives vs.&nbsp;23% preposed and 77% postposed genitives; in
articular phrases: 4% preposed, 18% internal, 78% postposed
non-articular genitives vs.&nbsp;3% preposed, 17% internal and 80% postposed
articular genitives.<a href="#fnref2" class="footnote-back" role="doc-backlink">↩︎</a></p></li>
